REMEMBER -DSA IS 80% PATTERN RECOGNITION AND 20% PROBLEM SPECIFIC TWIST 
IF U MASTER THE PATTERN,U WILL SOLVE 80% OF ANY INTERVIEW PROBLEM MUCH FASTER











üìÅ UNDIRECTED GRAPH PATTERNS



| Pattern                             | Purpose                                                                  |
| ----------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| üîπ Connected Components        | Identify distinct groups of connected nodes (e.g., islands, subnetworks) |
| üîπ Cycle Detection (Undirected) | Check for cycles using DFS or Union-Find                                 |
| üîπ Union-Find (DSU)          | Efficiently manage dynamic connectivity of components                    |
| üîπ Minimum Spanning Tree (MST)  | Connect all nodes at minimal total cost (Prim‚Äôs or Kruskal‚Äôs algorithm)  |
| üîπ Bridge Finding (Tarjan)   | Find edges that, if removed, increase the number of components           |



üìÅ DIRECTED GRAPH PATTERNS


| Pattern                                    | Purpose                                                              |
| ------------------------------------------ | -------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| üî∏ **Topological Sort**                    | Linear ordering of nodes respecting direction (DAG only)             |
| üî∏ **Cycle Detection (Directed)**          | Detect cycles using recursion stack or indegree (Kahn‚Äôs algo)        |
| üî∏ **Strongly Connected Components (SCC)** | Identify cycles or closed subgraphs (Kosaraju or Tarjan‚Äôs algorithm) |
| üî∏ **DAG Shortest Path**                   | Find shortest/longest path in DAG using topological order            |
| üî∏ **Bellman-Ford Algorithm**              | Single-source shortest paths with support for negative weights       |


üìÅ COMMON TO BOTH (DIRECTED & UNDIRECTED)

| Pattern                          | Purpose                                                         |
| -------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------- |
| ‚úÖ **Breadth-First Search (BFS)** | Level-order traversal, unweighted shortest paths                |
| ‚úÖ **Depth-First Search (DFS)**   | Deep exploration, useful for pathfinding, cycles, components    |
| ‚úÖ **Dijkstra‚Äôs Algorithm**       | Shortest path with non-negative edge weights                    |
| ‚úÖ **Floyd-Warshall Algorithm**   | All-pairs shortest paths (handles negative weights, not cycles) |
| ‚úÖ **0-1 BFS**                    | Optimized BFS for edge weights of 0 or 1 using deque            |
| ‚úÖ **Bidirectional BFS**          | BFS from both source and target for faster search               |
| ‚úÖ **Multi-Source BFS**           | Run BFS from multiple sources at once (e.g., fire/virus spread) |
| ‚úÖ **Backtracking on Graphs**     | Explore all paths recursively, used for constraints/paths       |






| Pattern                          | Time Complexity               |
| -------------------------------- | ----------------------------- |
| Connected Components (DFS/BFS)   | `O(V + E)`                    |
| Cycle Detection (Undirected)     | `O(V + E)` or `O(Œ±(N))` (DSU) |
| Union-Find (DSU with path comp.) | `O(Œ±(N))` per operation       |
| Minimum Spanning Tree (Kruskal)  | `O(E log V)`                  |
| Minimum Spanning Tree (Prim)     | `O(V¬≤)` or `O((V + E) log V)` |
| Bridge Finding (Tarjan)          | `O(V + E)`                    |
| Topological Sort                 | `O(V + E)`                    |
| Cycle Detection (Directed)       | `O(V + E)`                    |
| SCC (Kosaraju/Tarjan)            | `O(V + E)`                    |
| DAG Shortest Path                | `O(V + E)`                    |
| Bellman-Ford Algorithm           | `O(V √ó E)`                    |
| Breadth-First Search (BFS)       | `O(V + E)`                    |
| Depth-First Search (DFS)         | `O(V + E)`                    |
| Dijkstra‚Äôs Algorithm             | `O((V + E) log V)`            |
| Floyd-Warshall Algorithm         | `O(V¬≥)`                       |
| 0-1 BFS                          | `O(V + E)`                    |
| Bidirectional BFS                | `O(b^(d/2))` approx           |
| Multi-Source BFS                 | `O(V + E)`                    |
| Backtracking on Graphs           | `Exponential`                 |



